book.minejago.wiki.apis.advancement_trig:
This trigger is called when a player brews tea. It has one parameter:
- "potion": The potion ID.
Minejago adds a few advancement triggers for mods and datapacks to detect and use.
This trigger is called when a player activates spinjitzu. It has no parameters.
A generator for these triggers is available online [here](https://snapshot-jsons.thomasglasser.dev/advancement/).

This trigger is called when a player gets a element. It has one parameter:
- "element": The element ID.

This trigger is called when the status of the Skulkin raid changes. It has one parameter:
- "status": The status of the raid. This can be "started" or "won".
book.minejago.wiki.apis.data_maps.genera: A generator for these maps is available online [here](https://snapshot-jsons.thomasglasser.dev/partners/).
book.minejago.wiki.apis.data_maps.name: Data Maps
book.minejago.wiki.apis.data_maps.potion:
The potion drainables item map is used to define the drainability of items containing potions.
It stores the potion, the amount of cups, and the drained itemstack.
Note that the item should function as a potion, with the potion_contents component.
When adding entries, ensure the item works as intended.

The potion fillables item map is used to define the fillability of items containing potions.
It stores the amount of cups and the filled itemstack.
Note that the item should function as a potion, with the potion_contents component.
When adding entries, ensure the item works as intended.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.description: APIs in Minejago that allow for datapack and mod customization.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.elements.descrip:
Elements are data-driven, requiring a datapack and resource pack with a few simple files.
A generator for these elements is available [here](https://jsons.thomasglasser.dev/minejago/element/).
book.minejago.wiki.apis.elements.generat: A generator for these elements is available online [here](https://snapshot-jsons.thomasglasser.dev/minejago/element/).
book.minejago.wiki.apis.elements.guide.t: A guide for creating elements can be found [here](https://snapshot-jsons.thomasglasser.dev/guides/element/).
book.minejago.wiki.apis.elements.name: Elements
Focus modifiers are a data-driven way for data packs and mods to alter the amount of focus gained during meditation depending on a variety of factors.

Focus modifiers have a type that determines what they apply to.
The following types are available:
- block
- entity
- item
- location
- world\
The "modifier" field specifies the amount of focus to modify the base amount by. This can be a positive or negative decimal number.\
The "operation" field specifies how to modify the focus.
The following operations are available:
- addition
- subtraction
- multiplication
- division
A generator for these modifiers is available online [here](https://snapshot-jsons.thomasglasser.dev/partners/).
book.minejago.wiki.apis.name: APIs
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.biome.text: There are biome tags for the mod's structures and trees. You can add other biomes to these tags for compatibility with biome mods.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.biome.title: Biomes
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.block.text: There is a block tag for the mod's teapots. This tag can be used to add teapot variants.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.block.title: Blocks
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.damage_type: There is a damage type tag for Golden Weapons to determine if weapons can be damaged by certain damage types.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.description: Minejago adds a few tags that can expand functionality of addons.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.element.tex:
There are element tags for the elemental powers used by Golden Weapons.
These can be used to allow custom powers to use a Golden Weapon.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.entity_type:
There are entity type tags for the mod's entity categories, such as Skulkins and Dragons.
These can be used to add more variants of these entities.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.generator.t: A generator for vanilla tags is available online [here](https://snapshot-jsons.thomasglasser.dev/generators/) and for mod tags [here](https://snapshot-jsons.thomasglasser.dev/partners/).
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.item.text:
There are item tags for the mod's items, such as Golden Weapons, Dragon Foods, and Gi.
These can be used to add more variants of these items.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.item.title: Items
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.name: Tags
book.minejago.wiki.apis.tags.structure.t:
There are structure tags for the mod's structures, such as Ninjago City or Golden Weapon structures.
These can be used to add more variants of these structures.
book.minejago.wiki.apis.teapot_brewing_r: Datapacks and mods are able to add new recipes to the teapot.

Teapot brewing recipes have the following fields:
- type: The type of recipe. In this case, it is "minejago:teapot_brewing".
- base: The base potion for the recipe.
- brewing_time: The time it takes to brew the tea in ticks.
- experience: The experience gained from brewing the tea.
- group: The recipe group. This value is useful for grouping similar recipes together.
- ingredient: The ingredient required to brew the tea.
- result: The resulting potion from brewing the tea.
A generator for recipes is available online [here](https://snapshot-jsons.thomasglasser.dev/recipe/).
book.minejago.wiki.characters.descriptio:
NPCs and other characters you'll meet in the world of Minejago.
They will fight back and defend other NPCs, so be careful!
They will also seek out and fight hostile mobs.
book.minejago.wiki.characters.name: Characters
book.minejago.wiki.characters.ninja_team:
Cole can be found in Mountain biomes.
He has the element of Earth.
He is a skilled climber,
so he is stronger, more durable, and can climb walls.

The Ninja Team is a group of NPCs that will help you in your journey.
They will fight back and defend other NPCs, so be careful!
They will also seek out and fight hostile mobs.

Jay can be found in [Ninjago City](entry://locations/ninjago_city).
He has the element of Lightning and wears an Elytra that he doesn't know how to use.

Kai can be found in the [Four Weapons Blacksmith](entry://locations/four_weapons).
He has the element of Fire.
When fighting, he wil don his iron armor and wield his iron sword.

Nya can be found in the [Four Weapons Blacksmith](entry://locations/four_weapons).
She currently has no element and is an unskilled fighter.

Master Wu is the leader of the Ninja Team.
He is wise and powerful, with maxed out stats.
He can be found in the [Monastery of Spinjitzu](entry://locations/monastery_of_spinjitzu).
He has the element of Creation and carries a Bamboo Staff.
This is a new item that can be crafted with bamboo and can be thrown.
He is responsible for giving players their [element](category://elements) and helping them unlock [Spinjitzu](category://spinjitzu).

Zane can be found in the Frozen River biome meditating underwater.
He has the element of Ice.
book.minejago.wiki.cosmetics.dev.configu:
The Development Team cosmetics have two client configuration options:
- "display_dev_team_cosmetic" - Whether or not to display the Development Team cosmetic.
- "display_legacy_dev_team_cosmetic" - Whether or not to display the Legacy Development Team cosmetic.
book.minejago.wiki.cosmetics.dev.descrip: Exclusive cosmetics for members of the Development Team.
Members of the development team that have been with the project since the beginning get access to an exclusive beard cosmetic.
book.minejago.wiki.cosmetics.dev.name: Development Team
book.minejago.wiki.cosmetics.name: Cosmetics
book.minejago.wiki.cosmetics.snapshot.co:
Snapshot Cosmetics have two client configuration options:
- "display_snapshot_tester_cosmetic" - Whether or not to display the Snapshot Tester cosmetic.
- "snapshot_tester_cosmetic_choice" - The cosmetic to display for the Snapshot Tester.
book.minejago.wiki.cosmetics.snapshot.de: Exclusive cosmetics for members of the Snapshot Program.
book.minejago.wiki.cosmetics.snapshot.pi: Testers for the pilot episodes get access to a Bamboo Hat cosmetic.
book.minejago.wiki.decorations.descripti: Decorative blocks to make your world look nice.
book.minejago.wiki.decorations.name: Decorations
book.minejago.wiki.decorations.paintings: Decorative paintings to hang on your walls.
The mod adds a variety of placeable paintings that can be used to brighten up your world.
There are also paintings that generate as part of structures in the world that can not be placed by the player.
book.minejago.wiki.decorations.scroll.de: The scroll item and block family can be a wonderful decoration and writing tool for your world.
book.minejago.wiki.decorations.scroll.sc: The scroll shelf is a decorative block that also amplifies focus gain.
book.minejago.wiki.decorations.scroll.wr:
The writable scroll is an item that can be written on and read.
It can be placed in an chiseled scroll shelf for decoration or in a lectern for reading.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.descript: Mods that are not required but enhance the Minejago experience.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.jade.des: Jade is the information HUD mod.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.jade.ele: [Jade](https://modrinth.com/mod/jade) is able to show the element information of living entities.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.jade.gol: [Jade](https://modrinth.com/mod/jade) is able to show whether a Four Weapons sign contains a Golden Weapons Map.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.jade.tea: [Jade](https://modrinth.com/mod/jade) is able to show the contents and brewing information of a teapot.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.jei.desc: Just Enough Items is an item and recipe viewing mod.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.jei.name: Just Enough Items
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.jei.teap: [Just Enough Items](https://modrinth.com/mod/jei) is able to show the recipes of a teapot.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.modonomi: Modonomicon is an in-game documentation mod.
[Modonomicon](https://modrinth.com/mod/modonomicon) provides an in-game wiki for Minejago.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.name: Optional Dependencies
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.playeran: playerAnimator is a player animation library.
There are special animations for using the [Golden Weapons](entry://elements/golden_weapons) with [playerAnimator](https://modrinth.com/mod/playeranimator) installed.
There are special animations for [Spinjitzu](category://spinjitzu) that are shown with [playerAnimator](https://modrinth.com/mod/playeranimator) installed.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.ryoamicl: RyoamicLights is a dynamic lights mod.
[Golden Weapons](entry://elements/golden_weapons) emit light when [RyoamicLights](https://modrinth.com/mod/ryoamiclights) is installed.
book.minejago.wiki.dependencies.tslatent: TslatEntityStatus is a mod to view entity health and other statuses.
[TslatEntityStatus](https://modrinth.com/mod/tslatentitystatus) is able to show the element information of living entities.
book.minejago.wiki.description: Thank you for installing Minejago! Within these pages is everything you'll ever need to know about the mod, from how to tame a dragon to how to fight the Overlord. Check back here when new updates come out to see the changes!
book.minejago.wiki.elements.configuratio:
The "/element" command is used to query, give, and clear elements.
It has 3 functions:
- "/element <entity>": Query the element of an entity.
- "/element <element> <entity>": Give a element to an entity.
- "/element clear <entity>": Clear the element of an entity.
The entity argument can be omitted to apply the command to the sender.
Values changeable via the config screen that alter gameplay.

There are four config values for elements:
- "allow_choose" (default: false): Whether players can choose their element.
- "allow_change" (default: false): Whether players can change their element.
- "drain_pool" (default: true): Whether Wu can only give a element once before all elements are given.
- "enable_no_element" (default: true): Whether players can be given no element.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.description: Super abilities relating to an element that can be discovered and used by the player.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.discovery.ch:
Depending on [config values](entry://elements/configuration) set, players may have the option to choose or change their element.
Choosing one's element involves interacting with [Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu) and selecting from the Element Selection Screen.
Changing one's element involves interacting with [Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu) after already having a element to get a new one.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.discovery.de: The process of discovering one's element.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.discovery.fi:
To discover one's element,
the player must first find [Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu) in the [Monastery of Spinjitzu](entry://locations/monastery_of_spinjitzu) and present him the [Golden Weapons map](entry://locations/four_weapons@golden_weapons_map).
Wu will then spinjitzu over to the player and tell them their element.
He will also give them their [Training Gi](entry://elements/gi@training).
book.minejago.wiki.elements.dragons.abou:
Dragons can be found protecting the [Golden Weapons locations](category://locations).
They will defend themselves and their [Golden Weapon](entry://elements/golden_weapons) if provoked.
They will also fight monsters and other hostile mobs.
They can shoot projectiles and fight up close.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.dragons.bond:
To bond with and tame a dragon, you can feed it food and treats and interact with it.
Any dragon can be bonded with, even if tamed or of another element.
Bonding and taming dragons requires [focus](category://focus) and patience.
Once the bond is high enough,
you can tame a dragon with a matching element.
Once tamed, you can equip the dragon with a saddle and chest and fly it around.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.dragons.desc: Powerful creatures that protect the Golden Weapons and their wielders and can travel between worlds
book.minejago.wiki.elements.dragons.name: Dragons
book.minejago.wiki.elements.gi.abilities:
Gi are made for stealth,
so wearing them will make you undetectable around vibration detectors.
You will also be able to walk on powdered snow.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.gi.black.tex:
The Black Gi is the most basic Gi.
It is not associated with any element and is given by [Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu) when training begins.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.gi.creative_: All mod and datapack Gi can be found in the Gi tab
book.minejago.wiki.elements.gi.descripti: Garments worn by ninja to increase their stealth and defense.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.gi.name: Gi
The Training Gi is the first Gi you will receive after discovering your elemental element.
It is functionally no different from the Black Gi.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.golden_weapo: Weapons created by the First Spinjitzu Master to harness the element of the elements

The Scythe of Quakes is a powerful weapon of the Earth element found in the [Cave of Despair](entry://locations/cave_of_despair).
It can be used to manipulate the ground.

It currently has three unique abilities:
- By right-clicking solid ground,
the scythe will send a beam of rocks to make a path into the Earth.
You are unable to move during this time.
- By crouching and right-clicking solid ground,
the scythe will send a circle of explosions that will destroy the ground around you.
This will damage nearby entities, but may also damage you.
- By right-clicking ground with air below it,
the scythe will pull nearby blocks down to the ground and make them fall.
This can be useful for mining, creating traps, or making a quick escape.
Each Golden Weapon has unique abilities that can be used by interacting with the air, the ground, or other entities.
book.minejago.wiki.elements.name: Elements
book.minejago.wiki.expansions.descriptio: Official expansion mods and packs that enhance the Minejago experience.
The Immersion Pack is a resource pack that enhances the Minejago experience for aesthetic and roleplay purposes.
All references of the Note Block have been renamed to Drum and the block has been made to resemble the drum from the pilots.
The Light Blue Teapot and Teacup found in the [Monastery of Spinjitzu](entry://locations/monastery_of_spinjitzu) have been retextured to look more like Wu's.
book.minejago.wiki.expansions.name: Expansions
book.minejago.wiki.expansions.potion_pot: The Potion Pot Pack is a datapack that allows brewing vanilla potions in teapots

Making vanilla tea involves using the same ingredients as the brewing stand.
For example, adding nether wart to water in a teapot will create Awkward Tea.
Adding a fermented spider eye to Awkward Tea will create Weakness Tea.
book.minejago.wiki.focus.description:
A new gameplay mechanic that allows you to focus your energy to gain powerful abilities.
The bar is tinted to your element color.
By default, the bar is placed above your hunger bar, but this can be changed in the client config.
book.minejago.wiki.focus.meditation.desc: Meditation is a new mechanic that increases your focus over time.
book.minejago.wiki.focus.meditation.mega:
When in peak physical and mental condition, you can enter a state of Mega Meditation.
This state is achieved by having full health, hunger, and focus.
While in this state, you will gain focus at a decreased rate,
but the focus gained will last longer.
\
Mega Meditation can not be achieved with the [Hyperfocus effect](entry://focus/tea@hyperfocus).
book.minejago.wiki.focus.meditation.modi:
The following is a list of default modifiers that are included with the mod:
- Biomes
    - The Meadow adds 0.2 focus
- Blocks
    - Lit Candles add 0.25 focus per candle nearby
    - Water adds 0.05 focus per block nearby
    - Enchanted Wood adds 0.25 focus per block nearby
    - Scroll Shelves add 0.2 focus per block nearby
- Dimensions
    - The End adds 1 focus
    - The Nether subtracts 1 focus

- Items
    - The Golden Weapons add 0.5 focus per item in the inventory or nearby
- World Properties
    - Night adds 0.5 focus
    - Dawn and Dusk add 1 focus
    - Being at a Y level above 100 adds 1 focus
    - Thunderstorms multiply all focus gained by 1.5
    - Rain multiplies all focus gained by 1.25
book.minejago.wiki.focus.meditation.name: Meditation
book.minejago.wiki.focus.name: Focus
book.minejago.wiki.focus.tea.description: Focus Tea is a drink that helps you focus and concentrate.
Hyperfocus is a new potion effect that increases the player's focus and concentration.
The value depends on the amplifier of the potion effect.
It is instantaneously applied when the player drinks Focus Tea.
book.minejago.wiki.focus.tea.name: Focus Tea
book.minejago.wiki.focus.tea.tree.text:
Focus Trees can be found in meadows.
They are a source of Enchanted Wood and Focus Leaves.
Focus Leaves can be harvested with Shears and brewed in a [teapot](entry://tea/teapot) to make Focus Tea.
book.minejago.wiki.focus.tea.tree.title: Focus Tree
book.minejago.wiki.focus.using.descripti: Focus is decreased by using mod abilities. There are also level requirements for some abilities.
book.minejago.wiki.focus.using.dragon.te:
Bonding with a dragon requires 10 focus and will consume 3.0 focus.
Taming a dragon requires 18 focus and will consume 6.0 focus.
book.minejago.wiki.focus.using.golden_we: Using a Golden Weapon requires 4 focus and will consume 2.0 focus.
If a player hasn't slept for 1 day, they will start to lose focus rapidly.
This will consume 1.0 focus per tick.
book.minejago.wiki.focus.using.name: Using Focus
book.minejago.wiki.focus.using.spinjitzu:
Learning Spinjitzu requires 6 focus and will consume 2.5 focus.
Using Spinjitzu requires 6 focus and will consume 0.1 focus.
book.minejago.wiki.locations.cave_of_des:
The Cave of Despair is the location of the Scythe of Quakes and the Earth Dragon.
It can be found in Badlands biomes.
If a Golden Weapons Map has been taken by the Skulkin,
they will also be seeking the Scythe,
and will try to stop you from reaching it.

The Cave of Despair is home to a variety of unique items.
In suspicious red sand around the cave,
there is a chance to find one or more of the following items:
- Peaks Pottery Sherd
- Terrain Armor Trim Smithing Template
- Terracotta
- Light Gray Terracotta
- Clay Ball
- Emerald

To obtain the [Scythe of Quakes](entry://elements/golden_weapons@scythe_of_quakes),
you must interact with the [Earth Dragon](entry://elements/dragons)'s head in the center.
The Earth Dragon will then come out of the ground and try to protect the Scythe.
You must either tame or escape it to obtain the Scythe.
book.minejago.wiki.locations.description: The key places of the world of Minejago.
book.minejago.wiki.locations.four_weapon:
The home of Kai and Nya,
Four Weapons is a blacksmith shop.
It can be found in Plains biomes and it is the host of Skulkin Raids.

The Four Weapons blacksmith is home to a variety of unique items.
In a barrel by the entrance,
there is a chance to find one or more of the following items:
- Four Weapons Banner Pattern
- Four Weapons Armor Trim Smithing Template

The Four Weapons blacksmith is also home to [Kai](entry://characters/ninja_team@kai) and [Nya](entry://characters/ninja_team@nya).
They can be found in the shop walking around or outside defending the shop from enemies or [Skulkin Raids](entry://skulkin/raid).

The main purpose of the Four Weapons blacksmith is to store the Golden Weapons Map.
This map is a key item in the story of Minejago, as it leads to the locations of the Golden Weapons.
It can be found in the sign above the entrance.
Interacting with the sign will yield a filled map that leads to nearby Golden Weapons.
If no weapons are in a reasonable distance, no map will be generated.
There is one map per structure, so in order to find all four Golden Weapons,
you may need to find multiple Four Weapons structures.
book.minejago.wiki.locations.monastery_o:
The home of Master Wu,
the Monastery of Spinjitzu is a place of training, meditation, and relaxation.
It can be found in Mountain Peaks biomes.

The Monastery of Spinjitzu is home to a variety of unique items.
Throughout the Monastery, there are decorated pots using the Pottery Sherds Master, Yin Yang, Dragon's Head, and Dragon's Tail.
In a chest in [Master Wu's](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu) room,
there is a chance to find one or more of the following items:
- Lotus Armor Trim Smithing Template
- Ninja Banner Pattern

The Monastery of Spinjitzu is also home to [Master Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu).
He can be found in the Monastery walking around the Monastery or outside defending the Monastery from enemies.

The Spinjitzu Course is a training ground for learning [Spinjitzu](category://spinjitzu).
It is a series of obstacles that test the skills of a ninja.
It must be activated using a Dragon Button,
two of which can be found at the front of the Monastery.
One can practice the course for as long as they like,
but in order to unlock [Spinjitzu](category://spinjitzu),
they must interact with [Master Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu) and prompt him to begin drinking his tea.
He will then track the player as they complete the course.
If the player interacts with every element of the course and interacts with Wu again before he finishes his tea,
they will unlock Spinjitzu.
book.minejago.wiki.locations.name: Locations
book.minejago.wiki.locations.ninjago_cit:
Currently a small building in the wild,
Ninjago City will be a bustling metropolis in the future,
home to the characters of Minejago and their allies.

Ninjago City is currently the home of [Jay](entry://characters/ninja_team@jay).
He can be found on top of a skyscraper with a wrecked billboard.
book.minejago.wiki.name: Minejago Wiki
book.minejago.wiki.skills.agility.descri: Agility allows you to train your speed and jump height by running and jumping.

When sprinting and/or jumping, you train agility.
Every 100 seconds of sprinting or jumping (or 50 seconds if both sprinting and jumping), you gain 1 agility level.
As you level up, you will be able to sprint faster and jump higher.
book.minejago.wiki.skills.agility.name: Agility
book.minejago.wiki.skills.description:
A new gameplay mechanic that increases your stats as you train and level up.
Upon leveling up, you will hear a chime and see a message in the action bar.
Your stats will then increase by a small amount.
book.minejago.wiki.skills.dexterity.desc: Dexterity allows you to train your hand speed and damage by breaking blocks and attacking with your hands.

When breaking blocks or attacking with your hands, you train dexterity.
Every 100 damage points or blocks broken (can be less depending on break time), you gain 1 dexterity level.
As you level up, you will be able to break blocks and attack quicker and deal more damage while using your hands.
book.minejago.wiki.skills.dexterity.name: Dexterity
book.minejago.wiki.skills.name: Skills
book.minejago.wiki.skills.stealth.descri: Stealth allows you to train your sneaking ability by sneaking around mobs and vibration sensors.

When sneaking around mobs or vibration sensors, you train stealth.
Every 100 seconds of sneaking, you gain 1 stealth level.
As you level up, you will be able to sneak faster and become less detectable by mobs.
Once you reach level 10, you will become undetectable to vibration sensors.
book.minejago.wiki.skills.stealth.name: Stealth
book.minejago.wiki.skills.tool_proficien: Tool Proficiency allows you to train your tool speed and damage by breaking blocks and attacking with the proper tool.

When breaking blocks or attacking with the proper tool, you train tool proficiency.
Every 100 damage points or blocks broken (can be less depending on break time), you gain 1 tool proficiency level.
As you level up, you will be able to break blocks and attack quicker and deal more damage while using tools.
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.description:
Skeletal creatures of the Underworld.
They can drop their armor and weapons on death.
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.name: Skulkin
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.normal.descri:
The most common type of Skulkin.
Lackeys of Samukai.
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.normal.name: Normal Skulkin
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.normal.varian:
There are four variants of the Normal Skulkin:
- The Knife variant wears black armor and wields a Bone Knife.
- The Bow variant wears white armor and wields a Bow.
- The Speed variant wears blue armor and runs faster than the other variants.
- The Strength variant wears red armor and is stronger than the other variants.
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.raid.configur:
There are two configuration options for the Skulkin Raid:
- "enable_tech" (default: true): Whether the Skulkin will ride on Skull Motorbikes and Skull Trucks or Skulkin Horses.
- "enable_skulkin_raids" (default: true): Whether the Skulkin will raid the [Four Weapons Blacksmith](entry://locations/four_weapons).
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.raid.descript:
A raid on the Four Weapons Blacksmith by the Skulkin searching for the Golden Weapons Map.
There are 4 waves of Skulkin, with Samukai leading the final wave.
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.raid.name: Skulkin Raid
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.raid.objectiv:
The main objective of the Skulkin Raid is to find the [Golden Weapons Map](entry://locations/four_weapons@golden_weapons_map) hidden in the [Four Weapons Blacksmith](entry://locations/four_weapons).
They will enter the structure and search block by block for the map.
They are rather stupid, so they may search the same block multiple times and take a while to find it.
If found, they will take it and exit into a portal, leaving the structure without a map.
After they take it, they will be found in the locations with the weapons and will try to take them.
Samukai is the leader of the Skulkin and will lead the final wave of the raid.
He throws knives when he is at low health and will always drop his chestplate on death.
book.minejago.wiki.skulkin.raid.vehicles:
During raids,
if the [tech config option](entry://skulkin/raid@configuration) is enabled,
Skulkin will ride on Skull Motorbikes,
and in the final wave,
Samukai, Nuckal, and Kruncha will ride on a Skull Truck.
If the [tech config option](entry://skulkin/raid@configuration) is disabled,
they will ride Skulkin Horses.
book.minejago.wiki.spinjitzu.abilities.a:
While doing Spinjitzu,
movement speed and attack knockback are increased,
allowing one to use momentum to their advantage.
book.minejago.wiki.spinjitzu.abilities.e:
While doing Spinjitzu,
users emit light and vibrations.
This make them more visible to mobs and sculk sensors.
Wearing a Gi will reduce visibility.
book.minejago.wiki.spinjitzu.abilities.p:
While doing Spinjitzu,
any entity that comes into contact with the user
will be knocked back,
forming a protective barrier around them.
book.minejago.wiki.spinjitzu.description: A martial art that involves the user spinning rapidly to create a tornado of energy. Toggled with 'N' by default.
book.minejago.wiki.spinjitzu.learning.co:
There are currently four configuration options for the Spinjitzu course:
- "require_course_completion" (default: true) - Whether the course must be completed to unlock Spinjitzu.
- "course_time_limit" (default: 30) - The time limit in seconds to complete the course.
- "course_radius" (default: 64) - The radius in blocks that [Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu) will check to find a teapot and include course elements
- "course_speed" (default: 0.5) - The speed at which the course elements rotate and move

The Spinjitzu course is a series of challenges designed to help you master Spinjitzu.
It is located in the center of the [Monastery of Spinjitzu](entry://locations/monastery_of_spinjitzu).,
and is the first step to becoming a Spinjitzu Master.
book.minejago.wiki.spinjitzu.learning.te:
When you feel you are ready, interact with [Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu) to begin the test.
He will sit down at his teapot and make tea while you run through the course.
If you complete the course and interact with him before he finishes his tea, you will unlock Spinjitzu.
If you run out of time, you will have to try again the next day.
\
It is possible to interrupt [Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu)'s tea-making process by hitting his cup with your hand or a projectile as he lifts it.
This will cause him to begin pouring tea again, giving you more time to complete the course.
book.minejago.wiki.spinjitzu.learning.tr:
To begin training, you must first activate the course.
You are able to run through the course as many times as you like,
but you must complete it in time with [Wu](entry://characters/ninja_team@wu) tracking you to become a Spinjitzu Master.
book.minejago.wiki.spinjitzu.name: Spinjitzu
book.minejago.wiki.support.contact.descr: Locations to contact the mod and its developers.

the [Discord](https://discord.gg/U6Qf4P9YW4) is the best place to go.
book.minejago.wiki.support.contact.email:
For business inquiries and other matters,
you can reach out to at [minejago@thomasglasser.dev](mailto:minejago@thomasglasser.dev).
book.minejago.wiki.support.contact.githu:
For issues and feature requests,
[GitHub](https://github.com/thomasglasser/Minejago/issues) is the best place to go.
book.minejago.wiki.support.contact.name: Contact
book.minejago.wiki.support.description: Finding, supporting, and getting help with Minejago.
book.minejago.wiki.support.donations.des: Locations to support the mod and its developers.
book.minejago.wiki.support.donations.lin:
If you would like to support the mod, you can do so [here](https://www.buymeacoffee.com/Minejago).
These funds will be put directly towards the development of the mod.
\
If you would like to support the developer, you can do so [here](https://www.buymeacoffee.com/thomasglasser).
These funds allow me to devote more time to the mod and other projects.
book.minejago.wiki.support.mod_pages.cur:
Though not recommended,
the mod can also be found on [CurseForge](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/minejago).
book.minejago.wiki.support.mod_pages.des: The locations the mod can be found and downloaded.
book.minejago.wiki.support.mod_pages.git:
The source code for the mod can be found on [GitHub](https://github.com/thomasglasser/Minejago).
This is also the place to report issues and suggest features.
book.minejago.wiki.support.mod_pages.mod: The main place to find and download the mod is on [Modrinth](https://modrinth.com/mod/minejago).
book.minejago.wiki.support.name: Support
book.minejago.wiki.support.wiki.descript: Locations to find information about the mod.
The mod has an in-game wiki when [Modonomicon](entry://dependencies/modonomicon) is installed.
This wiki contains information about the mod and its features.
book.minejago.wiki.support.wiki.name: Wiki
book.minejago.wiki.support.wiki.online.t: The wiki is also hosted online [here](https://minejago.wiki.thomasglasser.dev).
book.minejago.wiki.tea.description:
The drink of choice for many Masters of Spinjitzu, tea can be used as a refreshing drink or a powerful elixir.
Teas are made in the teapot with [data driven recipes](entry://apis/teapot_brewing_recipe) and can provide a variety of effects.
book.minejago.wiki.tea.magic.description: Teas that provide magical effects, made with magic leaves or other materials.
book.minejago.wiki.tea.magic.milk.text:
Milk can be boiled in a [teapot](entry://tea/teapot).
This drink gives you the Instant Cure effect that weakens all potion effects.
book.minejago.wiki.tea.magic.milk.title: Milk
book.minejago.wiki.tea.magic.minejago.te:
Focus Leaves can be brewed in water to make [Focus Tea](entry://focus/tea).
This tea gives you the [Hyperfocus effect](entry://focus/tea@hyperfocus).
book.minejago.wiki.tea.magic.name: Magic Tea
book.minejago.wiki.tea.magic.vanilla.tex:
If the [Potion Pot Pack](entry://expansions/potion_pot) is enabled,
you can brew vanilla teas in a [teapot](entry://tea/teapot) using vanilla ingredients.
Vanilla teas are less effective than corresponding potions,
but the recipe produces 6 cups instead of 1 bottle,
so the effects are spread out evenly.
book.minejago.wiki.tea.name: Tea
book.minejago.wiki.tea.regular.descripti: The most basic tea, made from normal leaves and water. These do not provide any special effects.
book.minejago.wiki.tea.regular.name: Regular Tea
book.minejago.wiki.tea.regular.vanilla.t:
Minejago adds regular tea for every vanilla leaf type.
These teas are made by combining the leaf with water in a teapot.
The teas are:
- Acacia Tea
- Oak Tea
- Cherry Tea
- Spruce Tea
- Mangrove Tea
- Jungle Tea
- Dark Oak Tea
- Birch Tea
- Azalea Tea
- Flowering Azalea Tea
book.minejago.wiki.tea.teapot.capacity.t:
Teapots can hold up to six cups of tea.
This is equivalent to two bottles or one bucket of tea.
It can be used as long as it has at least one cup of tea in it.
book.minejago.wiki.tea.teapot.descriptio:
Used to brew tea,
teapots can be carried around and placed wherever you need while keeping their contents.
There is no screen or recipe book, so making tea requires a bit of experimentation.
book.minejago.wiki.tea.teapot.name: Teapot

They keep their cool in the heat of battle,
and can keep their team in check.
